# The Plain Vanilla Tick Setup
[DefconQ: The Plain Architecture](defconq.tech/docs/architecture/plain)

TP(Ticker Plant)
- tick mode
- batch mode
- No `get` command. Use `-11!` instead to refer TP log file for prod
- TP log is composed by 3 parts, 
	- name of the update function on rt-subscriber
	- name of table to be updated
	- data

RDB(Real-time DB)
	To optimize query performance, add the g (grouped) attribute to the sym column of your tables.
```q
q) update sym:`g#sym from trade

q) meta trade
c     | t f a
------| -----
sym   | s   g
price | f
size  | i
time  | t
```

HDB(Histrocial DB)
	To optimize query performance, apply the p (parted) attribute on the sym column of your tables
